                <head>232. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On October 3, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> replied
                    to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_KN1">Kishi</persName>’s letter of
                    September 24 on the nuclear testing program. For texts of both letters, see
                    Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, October 21, 1957, pages 635
                    and 636, respectively. Documentation on the question of nuclear testing appears
                    in volume XIX. Additional documentation regarding Japan’s claims for damages
                    allegedly arising from the United States nuclear testing program is in
                    Department of State, Central Files 711.5611, 794.5, and 894.245.</p>
            </div>
